<p>My App setup icons for panes in status bar (class CMFCStatusBar). There is only one method for this task - CMFCStatusBar::SetPaneIcon(). But if icon have alpha channel this method loads wrong image (on black background).  I looked into the source code and I saw that CMFCStatusBar uses internal HIMAGELISTs for every panes. All this HIMAGELIST creates with flag ILC_MASK | ILC_COLORDDB, not ILC_COLOR32 or ILC_COLOR24. </p>  <p>This is a bug!</p>  <p>So, is there a way to use the icons with alpha channel in CMFCStatusBar panes?</p>  <p>Example:</p>  <pre><code>HICON hIcon = ::LoadImage(hModule, MAKEINTRESOURCE(nIconID), IMAGE_ICON, 16, 16, LR_DEFAULTCOLOR); m_StatusBar.SetPaneIcon(m_StatusBar.CommandToIndex(ID_INDICATOR_1), hIcon); </code></pre>